                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/1641</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Assistant Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Grady</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-20">January 20,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador called at my request and gave me the attached
                        memorandum<note n="12" xml:id="d7fn12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> of his oral statement to me with regard to the working of the navicert
                    system. I told him that we would study his memorandum and get in touch with him
                    later.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
